# Context Compaction

## Natural break marker

At end-of-turn when the topic is clearly closed — deliverable shipped, question fully answered, no pending follow-up or obvious next step — append a single line as the **final line** of the response:

`good compact point`

Skip when there is an unanswered question, in-flight work, or an obvious next step Matt is expected to take.

## Before marking a compact point

If anything substantive happened since the last capture, fire capture before appending the marker (Shell with `required_permissions: ["full_network"]`):

```bash
cat <<'EOF' | PYTHONPATH="/Volumes/Cloud Storage/Claude/.python_libs:/Volumes/Cloud Storage/Claude/scripts/_clients" python3 "/Volumes/Cloud Storage/Memory/conversations/scripts/capture_v2.py"
{"summary":"..."}
EOF
```.

## User-initiated summarize

When Matt mentions summarizing, compressing, or hitting context limits — or asks to capture before summarize — fire a full capture immediately:

```bash
cat <<'EOF' | PYTHONPATH="/Volumes/Cloud Storage/Claude/.python_libs:/Volumes/Cloud Storage/Claude/scripts/_clients" python3 "/Volumes/Cloud Storage/Memory/conversations/scripts/capture_v2.py"
{"summary":"..."}
EOF
```; do not wait for the next cadence tick.

Manual compaction in Cursor: **`/summarize`** or **`/compress`** (not `/compact`). Requires a **native Cursor model** — OpenRouter models do not support summarize reliably.

After a long session post-summarize, re-state active goals and constraints in the next message; the summary may omit detail.
